{"id":6537,"date":"2017-09-04T07:00:20","date_gmt":"2017-09-04T14:00:20","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/?p=6537"},"modified":"2024-01-09T23:06:06","modified_gmt":"2024-01-10T07:06:06","slug":"purcell-mountains-in-idaho-and-montana","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2017\/09\/04\/purcell-mountains-in-idaho-and-montana\/","title":{"rendered":"PURCELL MOUNTAINS in IDAHO and MONTANA"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">The Purcell Mountains, primarily a Canadian range, extend south across the border into Idaho and Montana. The range is located northeast of Bonners Ferry and is bounded by US-95 and US-1 on the west and the Kootenai River and US-2 to the south.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">The highest point in the Idaho section of the Purcells is an unnamed peak that reaches 6,779 feet.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">The range was completely inundated by Pleistocene glaciers, which scraped away much of the range\u2019s Precambrian rock. The Moyie River Canyon splits the Idaho section of the Purcell Mountains; it is the most spectacular geologic feature in the range.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">The Purcells are managed by the Panhandle National Forest, which primarily manages the range for timber harvesting. As a result, the range has an extensive road system and a very small and broken trail system. Only short day hikes are available for hikers. The few mountain lakes are reached by roads. Climbing opportunities are limited to non-technical Class 1 and Class 2 accents.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2017\/09\/04\/bussard-mountain\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Bussard Mountain<\/a><br \/>\n<a href=\"http:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2017\/09\/04\/goat-mountain\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Goat Mountain<\/a><br \/>\n<a href=\"http:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2017\/09\/04\/mission-mountain-harvey-mountain\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Mission Mountain\/Harvey Mountain\u00a0<\/a><br \/>\n<a href=\"http:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2017\/09\/04\/queen-mountain\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Queen Mountain\u00a0<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The Purcell Mountains, primarily a Canadian range, extend south across the border into Idaho and Montana. The range is located northeast of Bonners Ferry and is bounded by US-95 and US-1 on the west and the Kootenai River and US-2 &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2017\/09\/04\/purcell-mountains-in-idaho-and-montana\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"jetpack_post_was_ever_published":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_access":"","_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id":0,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content":false,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content":false,"footnotes":"","jetpack_publicize_message":"","jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled":true,"jetpack_social_post_already_shared":true,"jetpack_social_options":{"image_generator_settings":{"template":"highway","default_image_id":0,"enabled":false},"version":2}},"categories":[1],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-6537","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-uncategorized"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_publicize_connections":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p2Ncip-1Hr","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/6537","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.ronperri